column2: The Speaker is the official who coordinates the day-to-day operations of the Senate. While the position has no political power, it is somewhat prestigious.
Ministers Without Portfolio have no official day to day duties, but still occupy a position of prestige and have the ear of the government.
The poet laureate is the official state poet, responsible for composing poems for special events and occasions.
